    "body": "### Problem\n\nw/o border:\r\n<img width=\"1508\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-06 at 3 54 57 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/5601392/d53c1eee-94c7-43a2-bb67-ea514565b590\">\r\n\r\nw/ border:\r\n<img width=\"1552\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-06 at 3 57 57 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/5601392/db78f2b6-091c-48cf-bb52-4337ceb496ff\">\r\n\r\nSeems like we just need to add an offset for border width. There's some similar logic in nvim-cmp that handles this correctly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nNo minimal config yet, but it involves\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.lsp.handlers[\"textDocument/hover\"] =\r\n  vim.lsp.with(vim.lsp.handlers.hover, {\r\n    border = \"single\",\r\n  })\r\n```\r\n\r\nI was thinking of looking at this myself, but if I don't get around to that then I'll post a full minimal config\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFloating window should not cover cursor\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nf67517bba\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno floating windows i think\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 13.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
